  "title": "Occupational Therapist (LOCUM/Full/Part time)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>MindChamps Allied Care, Child Therapy Centre in Singapore uses evidence-based practice, an integration of research evidence with clinical expertise and your child’s values and preference to achieve improved therapy outcomes. The MindChamps Allied Care team strongly believes in working closely with family to support your child’s development.</p><ul><li><a href=\"https: //mindchamps-alliedcare.com/book-appointment/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://mindchamps-alliedcare.com/</a></li></ul><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assess and deliver individualized Occupational Therapy interventions for children with diverse developmental challenges such as motor coordination disorder, sensory processing disorder, or autism spectrum disorder to improve functional outcomes.</li><li>Design and facilitate group Occupational Therapy classes focused on skills like handwriting and socialization to enhance peer interaction and developmental progress.</li><li>Communicate regularly with parents and caregivers by providing detailed updates on the child’s progress and actionable home strategies to support therapy goals.</li><li>Maintain current knowledge of advances in Paediatric Occupational Therapy to apply evidence-based practices effectively.</li><li>[LOCUM] Commit to weekend work (Saturday) to meet client scheduling needs.</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Full registration with Allied Health Professions Council (AHPC).</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma, Degree, or Masters in Occupational Therapy.</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills to engage effectively with children, families, and multidisciplinary teams.</li></ul>",
